-- ICT Group, Rostech in Joint Venture, Kommersant Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2013-04-25T15:47:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-25/ict-group-rostech-in-joint-venture-kommersant-says-correct-.html
(Corrects name of company in headline and first
paragraph.)  ICT Group and Russian state-owned
Rostech plan to invest at least $1b in a joint holding that
would extract and refine rare-earth metals at the Tomtor deposit
in Yakutia,  Kommersant  reported, citing unidentified people
familiar with the project.
* Ist Group will hold 50% plus 1 share in JV and state co. will
get 25% plus 1 share with the rest going to an investment fund:
Kommersant
* New JV will also handle, monazite storage in Krasnoufimsk in
Ural region and a hydro-metallurgical plant that would process
4,500 t of ferro-niobium and 10,000 t of rare-earth oxides a yr:
Kommersant
* Govt will offer license for Tomtor deposit development to
investors this yr:  Kommersant  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
